Source: Channel News Asia [edited]
<http://www.channelnewsasia.com/stories/singaporelocalnews/view/70003/1/.html>

Singapore suspends all poultry imports from US after avian influenza outbreak
--------------------------------------------------
Singapore has suspended all imports of poultry products from the United
States effective immediately.
The move comes after officials in the US state of Delaware confirmed the
outbreak of avian influenza and ordered the culling of some 12,000 chickens.
US officials said the flu strain was different from the one that has spread
to humans in Asia. The Agri-Food and Veterinary Authority (AVA) said
Singapore's chicken supply would not be severely affected, since imports
from the United States account for only about 9 percent of total consumption.
Brazil now supplies over 50 percent of Singapore's frozen chicken meat. AVA
is encouraging affected businesses to import poultry from its list of 11
approved countries such as Australia, New Zealand, and Canada.
The AVA is banning US imports of all live birds, day-old chicks, and frozen
poultry.
[Byline: Ken Teh]
