[Avian influenza has various strains. H7 is a poultry strain and -- unlike
the H5 strain -- has not been shown to cross to humans and cause severe
illness except in very rare instances (see 20030501.1092 in the see alsos).
H7 has caused conjunctivitis and other upper respiratory tract symptoms in
humans (see 20030501.1092 in the see alsos). However, Avian influenza is
considered a serious disease in the poultry industry.
It is interesting to note that in posting 20040206.0432, a representative
of Elanco Animal Health went to the farm. This could imply that upon
initial investigation, there was some thought it could be a drug reaction
from an Elanco product. - Mod.TG/DK]
